  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>We've talked about coordinating OpenHatch groups a couple of times.  I'm hereby
codifying the idea.

An OpenHatch group would be a group of people who meet at some periodic basis to
hang out and work on OpenHatch-related things.  The group could be location
based (OpenHatch Philly, OpenHatch Chelmsford, OpenHatch Internet, ...) or it
could be topic based (OpenHatch Python [for python-related projects], OpenHatch
Docs, OpenHatch Database Sanity, ...), or some other slicing (OpenHatch Things
We Can Do In Emacs, OpenHatch Free Software, OpenHatch GNU, ...).  Or something
like that--I don't think anyone's mentioned a requirement for structure or anything.

What would be needed from the OpenHatch site to make this work better would be:

1. a page on the OpenHatch site listing all the registered OpenHatch groups and
for each group, some details on how they coordinate themselves (meetup url, wiki
url, mailing list url, irc address, ...), description, ...

2. a launch page that talks about the existence of OpenHatch groups, what they
are, how to start your own and links to the groups listing page.

3. (optional) a way to indicate which OpenHatch groups you belong to on your
profile -- This isn't necessary, but it might be neat.

4. (optional) a calendar listing upcoming events -- I'm not sure how to do this
one without creating a lot of maintenance work for someone.


The goal here is not to build the infrastructure required to organize and run an
OpenHatch group (wikis, mailing lists, scheduling things, ...) but rather to
codify the existence of groups, provide a directory/listing of groups and how to
get involved, and provide some documentation on how to create your own and what
sorts of things work and what don't.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
